44:30.668 --> 44:32.569
The dreams, they're
more vivid, right?

44:34.072 --> 44:36.841
Yeah, your mind is more free
to create than an organic one.

44:36.842 --> 44:38.809
In fact, if I hadn't
fixed a small glitch,

44:38.810 --> 44:40.711
your brain wouldn't
be able to distinguish

44:40.712 --> 44:42.813
dreams from reality.

44:42.814 --> 44:44.281
Incredible, right?

44:44.282 --> 44:45.884
Look at this, look.

44:47.585 --> 44:49.053
See that?

44:49.054 --> 44:53.423
Every time I look at
these scans, I see growth.

44:53.424 --> 44:54.925
Very important.

44:54.926 --> 44:57.161
Look at all this growth,
all these new connections.

44:57.162 --> 44:59.596
It's amazing, actually.

44:59.597 --> 45:02.833
Looking at the mathematical
equivalent of your mind.

45:02.834 --> 45:04.969
You can see my thoughts?

45:04.970 --> 45:08.807
It's like looking at,
like a jpeg in binary.

45:09.841 --> 45:11.241
Yeah.

45:11.242 --> 45:15.079
Do you know, when I was
working on my thesis years ago,

45:15.080 --> 45:17.948
I spent two years
with a neurosurgeon.

45:17.949 --> 45:22.286
He likened the brain to more
of a plant than a computer.

45:22.287 --> 45:24.054
He said the task
of making a mind

45:24.055 --> 45:26.423
had nothing to do
with making it smart.

45:26.424 --> 45:28.525
You had to make something
that was capable

45:28.526 --> 45:30.260
of growing on its own.

45:30.261 --> 45:34.698
Like, even something so simple
as a tree or our flower.

45:34.699 --> 45:36.666
It's infinitely more...

45:39.771 --> 45:41.305
Hello?

45:41.306 --> 45:42.306
Hey?

45:43.408 --> 45:47.978
You're not paying attention.

45:47.979 --> 45:48.979
Sorry.

45:51.016 --> 45:52.950
Max, can you tell me something?

45:52.951 --> 45:54.052
Sure.

45:56.354 --> 45:58.957
Am I still able to be a wife?

46:03.761 --> 46:05.263
Yeah, of course.

46:06.431 --> 46:08.933
I designed your body
