46:08.934 --> 46:10.634
for sexual activity.

46:10.635 --> 46:11.668
You did?

46:11.669 --> 46:14.338
Yeah.

46:14.339 --> 46:15.339
Yeah.

46:16.908 --> 46:18.142
Yes.

46:19.410 --> 46:21.278
I used to head up a
love robot project.

46:21.279 --> 46:22.479
Can you believe that?

46:22.480 --> 46:25.951
I couldn't help but
pour a few things over.

46:27.418 --> 46:30.087
There's some things you're
gonna have to do to, um...

46:30.088 --> 46:32.157
prep the system, kind of.

46:33.491 --> 46:36.594
Ah, can we talk
about something else?

46:38.029 --> 46:41.899
I guess having children
is out of the question?

46:41.900 --> 46:42.900
Yeah.

46:53.611 --> 46:56.713
How long were
you married when it happened?

46:56.714 --> 46:58.849
Three months.

46:58.850 --> 47:02.954
Hm, well, any time is too
soon, but that is unfortunate.

47:04.589 --> 47:06.323
She had an aneurysm.

47:06.324 --> 47:07.925
It broke the connection
to her spinal cord

47:07.926 --> 47:10.995
but not enough to
damage the brain.

47:10.996 --> 47:14.131
I thought they could
just repair her.

47:14.132 --> 47:15.532
That's what they promised you?

47:15.533 --> 47:18.302
Not the way I thought.

47:18.303 --> 47:19.303
Hm.

47:21.339 --> 47:22.572
Well, Sam.

47:22.573 --> 47:24.741
Well, you're right to be
angry, Mr. Summerland,

47:24.742 --> 47:26.476
but for the wrong reasons.

47:26.477 --> 47:29.279
I want you to meet my chief
policy officer and advisor.

47:29.280 --> 47:30.280
Sam.

47:32.817 --> 47:36.053
Sam Patterson is an
old friend and he and I

47:36.054 --> 47:38.956
have followed Wesley's
developments for quite some time.

47:38.957 --> 47:40.557
Hi, Carter.

47:40.558 --> 47:42.026
The senator sent
me your message.

47:42.027 --> 47:43.860
I'm sorry to hear
what's happened here.

47:43.861 --> 47:47.164
This is why we have been
on this from the start.

47:47.165 --> 47:51.068
Carter, did they ask you a
lot of questions about Amelia?

47:51.069 --> 47:52.502
Of course.

47:52.503 --> 47:54.404
Did they ask you for
photographs of you together,

47:54.405 --> 47:56.006
private journals?

47:56.007 --> 47:57.241
Photos, yes.

47:57.242 --> 47:58.442
Journals, home movies?

47:58.443 --> 48:00.377
Yeah, whatever I
could get my hands on.

48:00.378 --> 48:04.015
They said it would help
return her memories.

48:05.616 --> 48:08.118
Is this a deposition?

48:08.119 --> 48:10.921
Are you familiar
with spiritual mediums?

48:10.922 --> 48:12.089
Excuse me?

48:12.090 --> 48:13.557
They use techniques
to fool people.

48:13.558 --> 48:16.760
They say general things
like, "I see a person dying"

48:16.761 --> 48:19.096
"from the chest," ooh.

48:19.097 --> 48:23.367
Well, most deaths do occur,
statistically, from the heart,

48:23.368 --> 48:25.102
so it's not a bad guess.

48:25.103 --> 48:28.138
But not to the
person who just lost

48:28.139 --> 48:29.573
a father to a heart attack.

48:29.574 --> 48:31.041
It's emotional manipulation.

48:31.042 --> 48:32.442
Carter, what they've built?

48:32.443 --> 48:34.144
It's not your wife.

48:34.145 --> 48:35.345
It's an imitation.

48:35.346 --> 48:37.248
You believe it because,

48:38.816 --> 48:41.251
well, you wanna believe it.

48:41.252 --> 48:43.887
They're counting on
people to react that way

48:43.888 --> 48:46.056
in order to sell
what they wanna sell.

48:46.057 --> 48:47.225
Immortality.

48:48.659 --> 48:50.827
People will pay
ungodly amounts of money

48:50.828 --> 48:53.230
to have a chance
to fly in space.

48:53.231 --> 48:56.633
You think they won't pay at
least a million for this?

48:56.634 --> 48:58.102
Carter, most live
their lives day to day,

48:58.103 --> 49:02.406
like you I imagine,
until something happens.

49:02.407 --> 49:04.008
You're dancing through
a big beautiful field

49:04.009 --> 49:07.077
and then suddenly a
snake jumps out and bites

49:07.078 --> 49:11.249
and the reality of our fragile
lives is suddenly exposed.

49:12.817 --> 49:15.986
We run to the one thing that
we understand to be true.

49:15.987 --> 49:17.021
Well, I don't know
what's true here,

49:17.022 --> 49:18.255
but I know what's not.

49:18.256 --> 49:22.359
For now, you can fix
this if you help us.

49:26.597 --> 49:28.765
If Congress passes
the Humanity Act

49:28.766 --> 49:31.335
it will become illegal
to copy or sell

49:31.336 --> 49:34.771
any element of the human
brain for monetary gain?

49:34.772 --> 49:36.306
Correct.

49:36.307 --> 49:38.942
I think the most obvious
critique of your viewpoint

49:38.943 --> 49:42.112
is that it forbids others
from making a choice.

49:42.113 --> 49:44.114
It's a false choice.

49:44.115 --> 49:46.383
It's something that takes
advantage of people.

49:46.384 --> 49:49.120
Mr. Summerland
can speak to that.

49:50.055 --> 49:52.623
Mr. Summerland?

50:01.732 --> 50:03.234
What she is now,

50:05.903 --> 50:07.004
it's not her.

50:10.541 --> 50:12.043
They took my wife.

50:16.013 --> 50:19.816
Carter, you said that
they took your wife.

50:19.817 --> 50:23.687
I assume you signed consent
papers, did you not?

50:23.688 --> 50:24.821
She was dying.

50:24.822 --> 50:26.223
I didn't know what to do.

50:26.224 --> 50:28.158
I think that most
people would question

50:28.159 --> 50:30.627
why you signed in
the first place.

50:30.628 --> 50:35.332
Well then, you have no
idea what it feels like.

50:35.333 --> 50:38.268
We need to change
the spin on this.

50:38.269 --> 50:40.437
I got a call from Adah Allen's
producers this morning.

50:40.438 --> 50:42.806
They want a one-on-one
interview with Amelia.

50:42.807 --> 50:44.909
No way, absolutely not.

50:46.477 --> 50:48.212
Of course you're okay with this.

50:48.213 --> 50:50.080
We need to get ahead of
William somehow, otherwise...

50:50.081 --> 50:52.516
We are not having this
conversation again, Paul.

50:52.517 --> 50:55.485
In 12 years you
have not ever once

50:55.486 --> 50:57.987
rushed one of my projects, ever.

50:57.988 --> 50:59.256
Which is why you
need to humor me.

50:59.257 --> 51:01.658
For 12 years I funded
this humanitarian work.

51:01.659 --> 51:03.460
Don't make this about
the goddamn money, Paul.

51:03.461 --> 51:05.395
I've given you a full
staff with technicians

51:05.396 --> 51:07.931
for four years, not to mention
the cost with prototypes

51:07.932 --> 51:09.533
and materials and
security and mark...

51:09.534 --> 51:11.501
The work we are doing takes time

51:11.502 --> 51:12.902
and you need to respect that.

51:12.903 --> 51:14.238
We don't have
the luxury of time.

51:14.239 --> 51:16.106
Paul we are making
progress, but you...

51:16.107 --> 51:17.108
No, Ellen!

51:19.644 --> 51:21.479
Do not destroy this.

51:30.555 --> 51:33.124
Just get Amelia ready.

51:36.194 --> 51:38.662
Got big news today.

51:38.663 --> 51:41.398
It has been exactly
six months this week

51:41.399 --> 51:43.267
since I stopped energy drinks.

51:43.268 --> 51:46.836
And I've been taking
lunch to work.

52:00.985 --> 52:01.985
I had...

52:03.888 --> 52:05.055
another dream.

52:06.324 --> 52:09.594
Okay, why don't
you tell me about it.

52:11.662 --> 52:13.331
I remember Carter.

52:15.032 --> 52:16.867
I remember everything.

52:20.671 --> 52:22.872
It's all come back.

52:22.873 --> 52:23.873
Everything.

52:24.742 --> 52:25.743
Okay, wow.

52:28.813 --> 52:29.813
Wow!

52:31.282 --> 52:32.282
Okay.

52:33.784 --> 52:36.753
I need to leave this place.

52:36.754 --> 52:39.022
I need to find my husband.

52:39.023 --> 52:40.858
Okay, shh, shh, shh.

52:44.729 --> 52:45.729
Okay.

54:03.240 --> 54:04.240
Hello?

54:08.112 --> 54:09.112
Carter?

54:14.585 --> 54:15.585
Yes?

54:17.522 --> 54:18.856
Where are you?

54:23.594 --> 54:24.828
Um...

54:24.829 --> 54:27.998
Carter, why haven't
you been to see me?

54:29.834 --> 54:31.401
I miss you.

54:31.402 --> 54:32.402
I love you.

55:10.408 --> 55:13.844
Beginning security lockdown.

55:26.691 --> 55:28.525
You are not allowed to do that.

55:28.526 --> 55:30.326
What do you mean I'm
not allowed to do that?

55:30.327 --> 55:32.929
Just like I'm not allowed
to contact Carter?

55:32.930 --> 55:34.831
God, what is wrong
with you people?

55:34.832 --> 55:37.167
You can't just keep me here.

55:42.573 --> 55:44.541
She doesn't log in
again for any reason,

55:44.542 --> 55:46.042
do you understand?

55:46.043 --> 55:48.311
I'm sorry, but how much
longer can we keep her here?

55:48.312 --> 55:49.713
You know what would
happen if she got out there.

55:49.714 --> 55:51.448
She doesn't have rights.

55:51.449 --> 55:53.684
Will you stop that, please?

56:00.357 --> 56:02.159
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight.

56:13.471 --> 56:15.672
I don't have rights?

56:15.673 --> 56:17.675
Amelia, you scared me.

56:23.347 --> 56:26.249
Can you appreciate the magnitude

56:26.250 --> 56:29.186
of everything that's
going on here?

56:30.421 --> 56:32.589
Now, you're saying
that electrical impulses

56:32.590 --> 56:33.657
in the brain...

56:33.658 --> 56:34.658
Oh, God.

56:35.392 --> 56:37.461
I hate television.

56:37.462 --> 56:41.297
I have to boil down
everything, all of the work,

56:41.298 --> 56:43.967
research, nuances,
discoveries, everything

56:43.968 --> 56:46.904
into something so
completely basic.

56:48.172 --> 56:49.173
It's stupid.

56:51.776 --> 56:53.277
But you know what?

56:56.514 --> 56:57.514
It worked.

56:58.749 --> 56:59.749
How?

57:01.852 --> 57:03.987
Every day we learn
new ways to conquer

57:03.988 --> 57:05.955
the limits of the human body,

57:05.956 --> 57:08.057
and yet there are still
so many barriers to cross.

57:08.058 --> 57:09.627
Goddamn it, Paul.

57:13.230 --> 57:17.767
How do you feel about going
on national television?

57:17.768 --> 57:20.771
Convincing the world
of what you are

57:21.972 --> 57:25.543
is the first step toward
your independence.

57:34.384 --> 57:35.384
Okay.

57:44.094 --> 57:48.098
We're very excited to
introduce you, you know?

57:50.635 --> 57:53.402
And, like magic, there she is.

57:53.403 --> 57:57.373
Adah Allen, I want you to
meet Amelia Summerland.

58:00.344 --> 58:01.979
Hello, Adah Allen.

58:08.719 --> 58:09.886
Paul, what is going on?

58:09.887 --> 58:11.254
You know what,
maybe we should not

58:11.255 --> 58:12.922
do this today.

58:12.923 --> 58:14.758
I'm totally messing with you.

58:14.759 --> 58:15.593
Totally messing with you.

58:15.593 --> 58:16.527
Hi, I'm Amelia.

58:16.528 --> 58:18.695
It's so nice to meet you.

58:18.696 --> 58:20.930
Decontamination complete.

58:20.931 --> 58:22.700
Welcome to my home.

58:24.101 --> 58:25.334
Your home?

58:25.335 --> 58:26.770
Well, yeah, for the time being.

58:26.771 --> 58:28.004
We have every intention
of returning Amelia

58:28.005 --> 58:30.439
to her life once
testing is finished.

58:30.440 --> 58:32.508
I think if you
interview Max and Ellen

58:32.509 --> 58:35.344
with Amelia alongside and
then do some demonstration...

58:35.345 --> 58:36.746
Yeah, that'll be a part of it,

58:36.747 --> 58:39.816
but I want to talk
to Amelia directly

58:39.817 --> 58:42.719
about her life now
and about Carter.

58:42.720 --> 58:44.253
No.

58:44.254 --> 58:46.723
I told you we can't do that,
not with a pending lawsuit.

58:46.724 --> 58:48.091
The viewers wanna know.

58:48.092 --> 58:49.793
We need to show the full Amelia.

58:49.794 --> 58:52.328
The story is about
Amelia, not the legal case.

58:52.329 --> 58:54.931
Exactly, the story's
supposed to be about Amelia.

58:54.932 --> 58:57.300
Her own husband doesn't
wanna talk to her,

58:57.301 --> 59:00.036
Congress is debating whether
to shut this program down.

59:00.037 --> 59:02.806
Come on, how do you expect
me not to talk about that?

59:02.807 --> 59:04.540
That topic is off limits.

59:04.541 --> 59:06.576
There's no point in us being
here if we don't get this.

59:06.577 --> 59:07.911
No, you're trying to paint some

59:07.912 --> 59:08.879
conspiracy here,
Okay, Paul you're wasting

59:08.879 --> 59:09.814
our time,

59:09.815 --> 59:11.247
and I'm not gonna let you.

59:11.248 --> 59:12.182
And painting a fake
picture of your corporation

59:12.183 --> 59:13.783
is the least of my concerns.

59:13.784 --> 59:14.752
And above all...

59:14.752 --> 59:15.752
Quiet!

59:18.088 --> 59:20.825
You've actually
talked to Carter?

59:22.126 --> 59:24.694
We thought that was
information best kept for later.

59:24.695 --> 59:27.330
This is why you blocked
my network access?

59:27.331 --> 59:28.165
Okay, enough.

59:28.166 --> 59:29.699
She's not doing this.

59:29.700 --> 59:32.135
You're concerned about some
soon to be forgotten lawsuit

59:32.136 --> 59:34.270
and we have the most
advanced scientific feat

59:34.271 --> 59:35.705
right here in front of us.

59:35.706 --> 59:39.843
We're concerned about whatever
Amelia is concerned about.

59:39.844 --> 59:42.747
That's what the
people want to see.

59:43.748 --> 59:46.016
I want to talk to Carter.

59:47.051 --> 59:49.986
Amelia, do this interview

59:49.987 --> 59:53.490
and you can tell Carter
whatever you want.

01:00:00.631 --> 01:00:04.368
Well, I guess it's in
your hands, Mr. Wesley.

01:00:11.709 --> 01:00:13.377
Get out of my way.

01:00:16.313 --> 01:00:17.546
Roll open.

01:00:17.547 --> 01:00:19.315
Stand by to dissolve
to one after the open.

01:00:19.316 --> 01:00:22.719
Challenge,
inspire, inform, and heal.

01:00:22.720 --> 01:00:24.488
It's Adah Allen Live.

01:00:27.825 --> 01:00:30.559
Amelia, thank you for
agreeing to do this interview.

01:00:30.560 --> 01:00:31.795
Thanks for comin' here.

01:00:31.796 --> 01:00:32.996
Thank you.

01:00:32.997 --> 01:00:36.733
I am nervous.

01:00:36.734 --> 01:00:38.168
Really? How so?

01:00:39.670 --> 01:00:41.270
Cameras.

01:00:41.271 --> 01:00:43.372
People watching, kind of, um,

01:00:43.373 --> 01:00:45.641
feeling the pressure, you know?

01:00:45.642 --> 01:00:48.712
What I actually mean is,
some people may be asking

01:00:48.713 --> 01:00:52.548
how it's possible for you
to even feel nervousness

01:00:52.549 --> 01:00:54.884
considering what you are.

01:00:54.885 --> 01:00:56.585
How did you feel
when you realized

01:00:56.586 --> 01:00:59.856
that you were no longer human?

01:00:59.857 --> 01:01:02.625
Kind of a loaded
question, don't you think?

01:01:02.626 --> 01:01:03.893
Why?

01:01:03.894 --> 01:01:06.696
'Cause it assumes that
I believe I'm not human.

01:01:06.697 --> 01:01:09.733
Yeah, but you are
not flesh and blood.

01:01:09.734 --> 01:01:10.901
No, I'm not.

01:01:12.336 --> 01:01:16.639
But human means different
things to different people.

01:01:16.640 --> 01:01:18.007
I would agree, actually.

01:01:18.008 --> 01:01:19.208
I would.

01:01:19.209 --> 01:01:20.443
So, then I'm gonna
rephrase that.

01:01:20.444 --> 01:01:23.246
How did it feel
when you realized

01:01:23.247 --> 01:01:25.582
that your old body was gone?

01:01:31.688 --> 01:01:32.757
Conflicted.

01:01:38.362 --> 01:01:39.362
It was...

01:01:42.332 --> 01:01:45.102
shocking to not
have a heartbeat.

01:01:51.041 --> 01:01:54.111
I didn't really like
myself at first.

01:01:56.113 --> 01:01:59.784
But then I remembered
that I spent two years

01:02:01.118 --> 01:02:04.288
in a hospital bed
watching the world go by.

01:02:07.892 --> 01:02:10.294
It's like I was dead already.

01:02:12.396 --> 01:02:14.464
So, to have a new body...

01:02:17.301 --> 01:02:19.804
And to be able to speak again.

01:02:21.271 --> 01:02:23.373
It's just this huge gift.

01:02:24.308 --> 01:02:25.742
I'm sure it is.

01:02:27.778 --> 01:02:29.445
But I think you would
agree that there

01:02:29.446 --> 01:02:31.280
are going to be people out there

01:02:31.281 --> 01:02:34.684
that are going to have
a challenging time

01:02:36.987 --> 01:02:40.490
in accepting you for
who and what you are.

01:02:42.092 --> 01:02:45.328
Some are calling you
a sin against God.

01:02:45.329 --> 01:02:46.863
And that's a direct quote

01:02:46.864 --> 01:02:50.900
from Republican Senator
Thaddeus Williams.

01:02:50.901 --> 01:02:52.601
- Really?
- Yes.

01:02:52.602 --> 01:02:54.770
Guess I'm not votin'
for him next fall.

01:02:56.006 --> 01:02:57.340
You have a wicked sense

01:02:57.341 --> 01:02:58.975
- of humor.
- I do.

01:02:58.976 --> 01:03:01.077
I would say that a
great sense of humor

01:03:01.078 --> 01:03:03.612
definitely makes us human,

01:03:03.613 --> 01:03:06.782
and certainly makes you
human in my opinion.

01:03:06.783 --> 01:03:09.485
But I'm gonna change
it up a little

01:03:09.486 --> 01:03:12.756
and ask you about
your husband, Carter.

01:03:15.425 --> 01:03:17.593
My husband's been through a lot.

01:03:17.594 --> 01:03:18.627
Well yeah, but to be fair,

01:03:18.628 --> 01:03:21.231
you've both been through a lot.

01:03:22.366 --> 01:03:23.300
Goodnight.

01:03:23.301 --> 01:03:25.234
And the last time he saw you

01:03:25.235 --> 01:03:29.238
you had quite a
catastrophic meltdown.

01:03:29.239 --> 01:03:31.074
